# Frontend Rules

## Technology Stack

- React Native (Expo SDK 55)
- React Navigation (bottom tabs)
- NativeWind (Tailwind for React Native)
- Zustand (state management)
- i18next (internationalization)

## Styling Rules

### Use NativeWind ONLY - NO Inline Styles

**CRITICAL:** All styling must use NativeWind className. Inline styles break RTL support.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
<View className="flex-1 bg-gray-50 p-4">
  <Text className="text-lg font-bold">Hello</Text>
</View>

// ❌ WRONG - Inline styles break RTL
<View style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: '#f9fafb', padding: 16 }}>
  <Text style={{ fontSize: 18, fontWeight: 'bold' }}>Hello</Text>
</View>
```

### NO Hardcoded Colors

**CRITICAL:** Use theme colors from `theme/colors.ts` for consistency.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { colors } from '../../theme';
<ActivityIndicator color={colors.primary} />

// ❌ WRONG - Hardcoded colors
<ActivityIndicator color="#3B82F6" />
<ActivityIndicator color="#0000ff" />
```

### RTL-Safe Directional Properties

**CRITICAL:** Never use left/right properties. Use NativeWind classes that auto-flip.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Auto-flips in RTL
<View className="ml-4">  // margin-left in LTR, margin-right in RTL
<View className="pl-2">  // padding-left in LTR, padding-right in RTL

// ❌ WRONG - Breaks RTL
<View style={{ marginLeft: 16 }}>
<View style={{ paddingLeft: 8 }}>
<View style={{ left: 0 }}>
<View style={{ right: 0 }}>
```

### Forbidden Patterns

These patterns will BREAK RTL support:

```typescript
// ❌ FORBIDDEN
style={{ marginLeft: 10 }}
style={{ marginRight: 10 }}
style={{ paddingLeft: 10 }}
style={{ paddingRight: 10 }}
style={{ left: 0 }}
style={{ right: 0 }}
style={{ textAlign: 'left' }}
style={{ textAlign: 'right' }}
style={{ color: '#000000' }}
style={{ backgroundColor: '#ffffff' }}
```

## Screen Rules

### Screens Must Be Thin

Screens are composition layers ONLY:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
export function GroupsScreen() {
  const { groups } = useAppStore();
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetchGroups(); // Service call
  }, []);

  return <View>...</View>;
}

// ❌ WRONG - Business logic in screen
export function GroupsScreen() {
  const [groups, setGroups] = useState([]);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    fetch('/api/groups')
      .then(res => res.json())
      .then(data => setGroups(data));
  }, []);

  return <View>...</View>;
}
```

## Services Layer

ALL data mutations go through services/:

```typescript
// services/groups.service.ts
export async function createGroup(dto: CreateGroupDto): Promise<Group | null> {
  const response = await apiPost<Group>('/groups', dto);
  
  if (response.success && response.data) {
    useAppStore.getState().addGroup(response.data);
    return response.data;
  }
  
  return null;
}
```

## State Management

Use Zustand for global state:

```typescript
const { groups, setGroups } = useAppStore();
```

## Internationalization

ALL text must use t():

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
<Text>{t('groups.title')}</Text>

// ❌ WRONG
<Text>Groups</Text>
```

## Component Rules

- Components in components/ must be reusable
- NO business logic in components
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Style with NativeWind
